ds on the angle\nbetween the permittivity gradient and the field polarisation. High pressure\ngenerates intense cylindrical shock/ rarefaction waves, which led to formation\nof void and compressed shell. We demonstrate that the Bessel beam proves to be\nan effective tool for producing extreme pressure/temperature conditions on the\nlaboratory tabletop. It appears that adjusting polarisation and permittivity\ngradient might be a novel way for increasing the maximum pressure. This tool\nallows for search of novel high-pressure material phases, for the 3D laser\nmachining and for creating Warm Dense Matter as those in star cores.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 28 Aug 2017 01:51:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 9 Oct 2017 04:52:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-10-10"}
