ce sample. The large error bars do not\nallow us to conclude whether OMC-2~FIR4 is a peculiar source. Nonetheless, an\nimportant result is that the measured HCO$^{+}$/N$_2$H$^{+}$ ratio does not\nvary with the source luminosity. At the present time, OMC-2 FIR4 remains the\nonly source where a high flux of energetic particles is clearly evident. More\nsensitive and higher angular resolution observations are required to further\ninvestigate this process.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 28 Aug 2017 09:29:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-13"}
